HEADWORD: northbound
<hw>northbound</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Moving toward the
north; <as>as, <ex>northbound</ex> traffic</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> northward.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>intended to be used by vehicles moving toward the
north; -- of roads and parts of roads; <as>as, The <ex>northbound</ex>
lane was blocked by an overturned tractor-trailer</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>North-Central</ent>⟦br⟧
